&quot;Old friiieeeeeennnnnnd!&nbsp; Hug me!&quot;
&quot;Whoa, you hug now?&quot;

I really made a reputation for myself back in the day.&nbsp; It's nice to have mostly gotten over myself.&nbsp; I&nbsp;usually have to command the other person to hug me before I get closer, just so I&nbsp;know the hug's on my terms, and they know my intent, but hey.&nbsp; Nobody's perfect.&nbsp; And the world still makes its repulsion for fat bodies clear enough that I'll never not find the process a little scary.

&nbsp;Stopped with a group outside a hipster dive. &nbsp;Everyone shuffles for IDs. &nbsp;I take longer than everyone else. &nbsp;

The bouncer. &nbsp;&quot;Ha, and you're the oldest of the bunch, huh?&quot;

Fuuuuuuuuuck this college town.

&quot;Athena, I've missed you!&nbsp; Let's chest bump.&quot;
Giggling.
&quot;I couldn't.&quot;
&quot;C'mon.&quot;
&quot;That'd be vulgar for me.&quot;
&quot;I know. &nbsp;For me, too.&quot;

&quot;My iTunes won't get CD&nbsp;track names.&nbsp; So much for downloaded the latest iTunes.&nbsp; Ugh!&nbsp; Anyway, how are you?&quot;
&quot;My Grandma died.&quot;
&quot;Well, I'd make you a mix tape, but...&quot;

Thank god I can censor.

&quot;She just hasn't called me since I bought her brunch 3 years ago.&quot;
&quot;Oh, is that what we ladies owe you for a meal?&nbsp; Those crazy feminists might have been up to something.&quot;
&quot;No, c'mon, I haven't been awake for brunch in ... longer than 3 years.&quot;
&quot;Oh?&quot;
&quot;It's a euphemism.&quot;
&quot;Oh?&quot;
&quot;SHE&nbsp;HASN'T&nbsp;CALLED&nbsp;ME&nbsp;SINCE&nbsp;WE&nbsp;FUCKED ALL&nbsp;NIGHT&nbsp;THREE&nbsp;YEARS&nbsp;AGO, GET&nbsp;IT?!&quot;
&quot;Brunch is not a euphemism.&quot;

Later
He sees the girl of brunch past, and promptly hangs on her arm for the next hour.

Later still
&quot;She's just one of those girls, get her drunk and she makes out with you.&nbsp; It's impolite to refuse.&quot;
&quot;Yes, and if there's anything we've learned about you today, it's that you're nothing if not a gentleman.&quot;

Girl, I love you, but making you feel a little guilty isn't enough for me not to memorialize this conversation forever.

Intro for the rest of you: all of this was said by one of the sweetest girls ever, and at her art opening no less.&nbsp; Hence I was completely unable to respond to any of it. 

&quot;You know that's THE&nbsp;GUY, right?&quot; (of my perpetual angst and broken DVD breakup)
&quot;WHAT?&quot;
&quot;Yeah.&quot;
&quot;But his girlfriend got me this show and they love each other more than anything!&quot;
...
&quot;I'm sure he didn't leave because of you, they just got back from a trip to Europe together.&nbsp; It's jet lag&quot;
...
&quot;But he's such a great guy.&quot;

Unemployed for months, underemployed for years, living off your parents for even longer, parents about to lose the house, and you're not willing to get a desk job?&nbsp; That's ridiculous.

Wait, that's offensive.&nbsp; Not so much for saying out loud.&nbsp; Oops.&nbsp; 

I&nbsp;apologized, said that maybe I just don't have any ideals, but I still think I've got better priorities.&nbsp;

&quot;No, when you don't pay attention to boys is when they realize they like you.&quot;
Insert scoffing noises
&quot;Whaaaat?&quot;
&quot;No, nevermind.&nbsp; You guys are the ones with boyfriends and chlamydia, what do I know.&quot;

I half/barely considered going up to Sacramento for the memorial service.&nbsp; But I'm not one for making scenes, and it would have been disrespectful to take the attention off of the deceased, besides.

I ended up going on a tour of Mountain View Cemetery the next day.&nbsp; 

Will I ever be able just say I'm an atheist, just matter-of-fact?&nbsp; I said it, if tentatively and my mom was &quot;sorry to hear that.&quot;&nbsp; Sort of like she felt she'd failed me, even though I've never heard her have a kind word for a church of any kind.

Maybe, were I not so godless, I wouldn't have called my grandmother a liar.&nbsp; Or as good as.&nbsp; Maybe I'd have more family.&nbsp; 

But then, I wouldn't have called her a liar if she hadn't told me my mother was the one making up stories.&nbsp; Like saying &quot;What? I never told your mother I never wanted to see you again because you were a disrespectful brat.&nbsp; At age twelve.&quot; is really gonna rekindle the familial love.&nbsp; 

Should I do that now?&nbsp; Just let it go, like it never happened?&nbsp; Would she even want that at this point?&nbsp; Do I?&nbsp; If I do, I have to do it before I leave California, ostensibly a year from now.&nbsp; Or before she follows her husband to the grave.
